eed 2<b>. Transfer to a sterilised jar and set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Topping"},{"content":"Towards the end of resting time, preheat oven to 220°C and grease two large baking trays."},{"content":"Tip dough out onto a lightly floured work surface and divide into two pieces. Roll each piece into a circle (approx. Ø 30 cm) and place one on each prepared  baking tray."},{"content":"Spread 2 Tbsp pesto over each pizza then arrange mozzarella, prosciutto and nectarines over the top. Scatter pizzas with fresh thyme leaves then bake for 12-15 minutes (220°C) until crust is lightly golden brown and cheese is melted."},{"content":"Scatter rocket over the top and drizzle with reserved balsamic reduction before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serves 4 as a main meal or 8 as a smaller lunch option.","Try basil or tomato pesto instead of red pepper pesto."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 35m","4 portions"]}